==Korean==
===Noun===
'''박쥐''' (''bagjwi, bakjwi'')
# [[bat]] cf. Middle English [[bakke]]

====Alternative spellings====
*[[밝쥐]] (''balgjwi, balkjwi'') (archaic, obsolete) literally, "bright (eyed) rat"  (not so true! But bats are more likely to be able to fly in the dark relying on [[echolocation]].)

====Synonyms====
*[[편복]] ([[蝙蝠]], ''pyeonbog, -bok'') 

====Antonyms====
*[[두더지]] (''dudeoji'') [[mole]] (almost blind!)

====Derived terms====
*박쥐[[구실]] (''-gusil'') [[opportunism]]
*박쥐[[우산]] (-[[雨傘]], ''-usan'')  [[umbrella]] (made of cloth)
*박쥐[[족]] (-[[族]], ''-jog, -jok'') [[nocturnal]]s 

====Related terms====
*[[밝다]] (''balg-da, balk-'') To be [[bright]]
*[[쥐]] (''jwi'') [[rat]] 

